Some angry Nigerians, on Saturday invaded the residence of Senator Teslim Folarin and carted away some valuables. Folarin, DAILY POST reports is representing Oyo Central district in the National Assembly. His house located at Oluyole area of Ibadan was burgled on Saturday. A source said the residents carted away motorcycles, fridges and television sets. Some pictures obtained by DAILY POST showed how the angry Nigerians were moving some property from the Senator’s house. However, all efforts made by DAILY POST to get Folarin proved abortive. Details later…